      • getPhysicalDeviceInformation

        GetPhysicalDeviceInformationResponse getPhysicalDeviceInformation(GetPhysicalDeviceInformation request)
                                                           throws CstaException
        The Get Physical Device Information service is used to obtain the current set of characteristics/capabilities associated with the physical element of a given device.

        Example: The following code gives an example of how to use getPhysicalDeviceInformation.
        Receiving the response is an indication that the request succeeded. 

         GetPhysicalDeviceInformation request = new GetPhysicalDeviceInformation(); 
 // device is a DeviceID that was retrieved 
 // using DeviceServices.getThirdPartyDeviceID(GetThirdPartyDeviceId)
 request.setDevice(device);
 GetPhysicalDeviceInformationResponse response = capabilityExchSvcs.getPhysicalDeviceInformation(request);
 // get the device data
 response.getDeviceCategory();
 response.getHasLogicalElement);
 response.getGroupDeviceAttributes();
        Parameters:
        request - A GetPhysicalDeviceInformation request that contains a DeviceID for the device that the service is requested.
        Returns:
        A GetPhysicalDeviceInformationResponse
        Throws:
        InvalidDeviceIDException - Thrown if an invalid Device ID has been specified.
        SecurityViolationException - Thrown if the user was not authorized to control the specified device.
        OperationException - Thrown if a logic error occurred in the code.
        CstaException - Thrown if an implementation specific error occurred.

      • getPhysicalDeviceName

        GetPhysicalDeviceNameResponse getPhysicalDeviceName(GetPhysicalDeviceName request)
                                             throws CstaException
        The Get Physical Device Name private request queries the switch with an extension of a device and receives the associated name of the device. The name is retrieved from the Communication Manager Integrated Directory Database. This service will allow an application to identify the names administered in Communication Manager with device extension numbers without maintaining its own database.

        Example: The following code gives an example of how to use getPhysicalDeviceName.
        Receiving the response is an indication that the request succeeded. 

         GetPhysicalDeviceInformation request = new GetPhysicalDeviceInformation(); 
 // device is a DeviceID that was retrieved 
 // using DeviceServices.getThirdPartyDeviceID(GetThirdPartyDeviceId)
 request.setDevice(device);
 GetPhysicalDeviceNameResponse response = capabilityExchSvcs.getPhysicalDeviceName(request);
 // get the device data
 response.getDeviceType();
 response.getName();
        Parameters:
        request - A GetPhysicalDeviceName request that contains a DeviceID for the device that the service is requested.
        Returns:
        A GetPhysicalDeviceNameResponse
        Throws:
        InvalidDeviceIDException - Thrown if an invalid Device ID has been specified.
        SecurityViolationException - Thrown if the user was not authorized to control the specified device.
        OperationException - Thrown if a logic error occurred in the code.
        CstaException - Thrown if an implementation specific error occurred.
